Lock calls:
| Line | Pattern | Context |
|------|---------|---------|
| 503 | `if let Ok(mut cache) = ANSI_CACHE.lock()` | ansi_codes() cache lookup |
| 513 | `if let Ok(mut cache) = ANSI_CACHE.lock()` | ansi_codes() cache insert |
| 575 | `if let Ok(mut cache) = CACHE.lock()` | parse() cache lookup |
| 583 | `if let Ok(mut cache) = CACHE.lock()` | parse() cache insert |

### src/cells.rs
One static Mutex cache:
```rust
static CELL_LEN_CACHE: LazyLock<Mutex<LruCache<String, usize>>> = ...;  // Line 17-18
```

Lock calls:
| Line | Pattern | Context |
|------|---------|---------|
| 53 | `if let Ok(mut cache) = CELL_LEN_CACHE.lock()` | cell_len() cache lookup |
| 63 | `if let Ok(mut cache) = CELL_LEN_CACHE.lock()` | cell_len() cache insert |

### src/color.rs
One static Mutex cache:
```rust
static CACHE: LazyLock<Mutex<LruCache<String, Color>>> = ...;  // Line 425-426
```

Lock calls:
| Line | Pattern | Context |
|------|---------|---------|
| 430 | `if let Ok(mut cache) = CACHE.lock()` | parse() cache lookup |
| 438 | `if let Ok(mut cache) = CACHE.lock()` | parse() cache insert |

## Migration Pattern

All cache modules follow the same pattern - try-cache-then-compute:

Before:
```rust
if let Ok(mut cache) = CACHE.lock() {
    if let Some(cached) = cache.get(&key) {
        return cached.clone();
    }
}
// Compute value...
if let Ok(mut cache) = CACHE.lock() {
    cache.put(key, value.clone());
}
value
```

After:
```rust
use crate::sync::lock_recover;

{
    let mut cache = lock_recover(&CACHE);
    if let Some(cached) = cache.get(&key) {
        return cached.clone();
    }
}
// Compute value...
{
    let mut cache = lock_recover(&CACHE);
    cache.put(key, value.clone());
}
value
```

