-{"id":"bd-288g","title":"Implement sync utility module for mutex helpers","description":"## Task Description

Create `src/sync.rs` module with consistent mutex handling utilities based on the approved RFC.

## Deliverables

### 1. Core Helpers

```rust
// src/sync.rs

use std::sync::{Mutex, MutexGuard, RwLock, RwLockReadGuard, RwLockWriteGuard};

/// Lock a mutex, recovering from poison if necessary.
/// 
/// # Behavior
/// - If the mutex is not poisoned, returns the guard normally
/// - If the mutex is poisoned (a thread panicked while holding it),
///   recovers the data and returns the guard anyway
/// 
/// # When to Use
/// - Production code where progress is more important than state integrity
/// - Caches where corruption just means stale data
/// 
/// # Example
/// ```rust
/// let mutex = Mutex::new(42);
/// let guard = lock_recover(&mutex);
/// assert_eq\!(*guard, 42);
/// ```
#[inline]
pub fn lock_recover<T>(mutex: &Mutex<T>) -> MutexGuard<T> {
    mutex.lock().unwrap_or_else(|e| e.into_inner())
}

/// Lock a mutex, logging on poison recovery in debug builds.
/// 
/// Same as `lock_recover` but prints a warning in debug builds
/// to help track down the source of poison.
#[inline]
pub fn lock_recover_debug<T>(mutex: &Mutex<T>, context: &str) -> MutexGuard<T> {
    mutex.lock().unwrap_or_else(|e| {
        #[cfg(debug_assertions)]
        eprintln\!("[mutex-poison] recovered at: {context}");
        e.into_inner()
    })
}

/// RwLock read guard with poison recovery
#[inline]
pub fn read_recover<T>(rwlock: &RwLock<T>) -> RwLockReadGuard<T> {
    rwlock.read().unwrap_or_else(|e| e.into_inner())
}

/// RwLock write guard with poison recovery
#[inline]
pub fn write_recover<T>(rwlock: &RwLock<T>) -> RwLockWriteGuard<T> {
    rwlock.write().unwrap_or_else(|e| e.into_inner())
}
```

### 2. Module Integration

Add to `src/lib.rs`:
```rust
mod sync;
pub use sync::{lock_recover, lock_recover_debug, read_recover, write_recover};
```

### 3. Unit Tests

```rust
#[cfg(test)]
mod tests {
    use super::*;
    use std::panic;

    #[test]
    fn test_lock_recover_normal() {
        let mutex = Mutex::new(42);
        let guard = lock_recover(&mutex);
        assert_eq\!(*guard, 42);
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_lock_recover_poisoned() {
        let mutex = Mutex::new(42);
        // Poison the mutex
        let _ = panic::catch_unwind(panic::AssertUnwindSafe(|| {
            let _guard = mutex.lock().unwrap();
            panic\!("intentional panic to poison mutex");
        }));
        // Should recover
        let guard = lock_recover(&mutex);
        assert_eq\!(*guard, 42);
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_read_recover_normal() {
        let rwlock = RwLock::new(42);
        let guard = read_recover(&rwlock);
        assert_eq\!(*guard, 42);
    }

    #[test]
    fn test_write_recover_normal() {
        let rwlock = RwLock::new(42);
        let mut guard = write_recover(&rwlock);
        *guard = 100;
        drop(guard);
        assert_eq\!(*read_recover(&rwlock), 100);
    }
}
```

